<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,898,1823]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345">
The taxonomic history of this genus is much complicated due to a number of nomenclatural procedures applied at various times, and by different authors, on multiple other genera. 
<bibRefCitation author="Lombardo" box="[988,1196,934,959]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" refString="Lombardo, F. (1999) Remarks on the genus Metriomantis Saussure &amp; Zehntner and descriptions of two new species and a new genus: Rehniella gen. n. (Insecta: Mantodea). Revue Suisse de Zoologie, 106, 393 - 405." type="journal article" year="1999">
Lombardo (
<number box="[1130,1188,935,959]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" value="1999.0">1999</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
recognized distinct morphological characters in 
<taxonomicName box="[473,777,970,995]" class="Insecta" family="Mantidae" genus="Metriomantis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mantodea" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="planicephala">
<emphasis box="[473,777,970,995]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="345">Metriomantis planicephala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, species that 
<bibRefCitation author="Rehn" box="[931,1073,970,995]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" refString="Rehn, J. A. G. (1916) The Stanford Expedition to Brazil, 1911 Dermaptera and Orthoptera I, Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia, 42, 257 - 266." type="journal article" year="1916">
Rehn (
<number box="[1006,1064,970,995]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" value="1916.0">1916</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
described from Gravatá, Ceará- 
<taxonomicName box="[151,226,1006,1031]" class="Insecta" family="Thespidae" genus="Chloromiopteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mantodea" pageId="10" pageNumber="356" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mirim">Mirim</taxonomicName>
, Rio Grande do Norte State (
<collectingCountry box="[581,652,1006,1031]" name="Brazil" pageId="10" pageNumber="345">Brazil</collectingCountry>
) (
<figureCitation box="[681,751,1006,1031]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1740,1762]" captionTargetBox="[166,1435,1214,1714]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,1213,1718]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 8. Metriomantis planicephala (now Photiomantis planicephala): a) holotype ♀, dorsal habitus, from Ceará-Mirim, Rio Grande do Norte, Brazil (ANSP). Photiomantis silvai (now Photiomantis planicephala): b) holotype ♂, dorsal habitus, from Piauí, Brazil (ESALQ). Margaromantis margaritaria (now Photiomantis planicephala): c) holotype ♂, dorsal habitus, from Petrolima, Pernambuco, Brazil (ESALQ)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/239055/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="345">
Fig. 
<number box="[738,751,1007,1031]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
a) and created a new genus to accommodate this species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Lombardo, 1999" authorityName="Lombardo" authorityYear="1999" box="[151,458,1042,1067]" class="Insecta" family="Mantidae" genus="Rehniella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mantodea" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,259,1042,1067]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="345">Rehniella</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lombardo" box="[267,458,1042,1067]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" refString="Lombardo, F. (1999) Remarks on the genus Metriomantis Saussure &amp; Zehntner and descriptions of two new species and a new genus: Rehniella gen. n. (Insecta: Mantodea). Revue Suisse de Zoologie, 106, 393 - 405." type="journal article" year="1999">
Lombardo, 
<number box="[399,458,1043,1067]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" value="1999.0">1999</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; however, this name was not available as it was preoccupied by 
<emphasis box="[1195,1309,1042,1067]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="345">
<taxonomicName box="[1195,1305,1042,1067]" class="Insecta" family="Mantidae" genus="Rehniella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mantodea" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Rehniella</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
a genus of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,257,1078,1103]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Gryllidae</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[273,398,1078,1103]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Orthoptera</taxonomicName>
) previosuly erected by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hebard" box="[667,837,1078,1103]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" refString="Hebard, M. (1928) The group Luzarae of the subfamily Phalangosinae (Orthoptera: Gryllidae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 54, 1 - 56." type="journal article" year="1928">
Hebard (
<number box="[767,828,1079,1103]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" value="1928.0">1928</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. This case of homonymy prompted 
<bibRefCitation author="Kocak" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" refString="Kocak, A. O. &amp; Kemal, M. (2008) (Dictyoptera: Mantidae). Two replacement names in the genus group taxa of Dictyoptera from Colombia and Arabian Peninsula. Centre for Entomological Studies Ankara, Miscellaneous Papers, 145, 8 - 9" type="journal article" year="2008">
Koçak &amp; Kemal (
<number box="[159,218,1115,1139]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" value="2008.0">2008</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Ozdikmen" box="[284,485,1114,1139]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" refString="Ozdikmen, H. (2008) A substitute name for Rehniella Lombardo, 1999 (Mantodea: Mantidae). Munis Entomology and Zoology, 3 (2), 765 - 766." type="journal article" year="2008">
Özdikmen (
<number box="[418,477,1115,1139]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" value="2008.0">2008</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
to propose, almost simultaneously, two replacement names, 
<emphasis box="[1184,1323,1114,1139]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="345">Colombiella</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kocak" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" refString="Kocak, A. O. &amp; Kemal, M. (2008) (Dictyoptera: Mantidae). Two replacement names in the genus group taxa of Dictyoptera from Colombia and Arabian Peninsula. Centre for Entomological Studies Ankara, Miscellaneous Papers, 145, 8 - 9" type="journal article" year="2008">
Koçak &amp; Kemal 
<number box="[234,290,1151,1175]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" value="2008.0">2008</number>
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<emphasis box="[347,477,1150,1175]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="345">Lombardoa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ozdikmen" box="[485,676,1150,1175]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" refString="Ozdikmen, H. (2008) A substitute name for Rehniella Lombardo, 1999 (Mantodea: Mantidae). Munis Entomology and Zoology, 3 (2), 765 - 766." type="journal article" year="2008">
Özdikmen, 
<number box="[618,676,1151,1175]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" value="2008.0">2008</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, with the former name having priority over the latter by just a few weeks of antecedence, thus making 
<taxonomicName authority="Rehn, 1916" authorityName="Rehn" authorityYear="1916" box="[564,1016,1186,1211]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" genus="Colombiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="planicephala">
<emphasis box="[564,857,1186,1211]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="345">Colombiella planicephala</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rehn" box="[874,1007,1186,1211]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" refString="Rehn, J. A. G. (1916) The Stanford Expedition to Brazil, 1911 Dermaptera and Orthoptera I, Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia, 42, 257 - 266." type="journal article" year="1916">
Rehn, 
<number box="[950,1007,1186,1211]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" value="1916.0">1916</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
the new valid name. 
<bibRefCitation author="Rivera" box="[1265,1436,1186,1211]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" refString="Rivera, J. (2010 a) Lost and Found: Rediscovery of the genus Margaromantis Piza, 1982 and the consequential nomenclatural changes in the genus Colombiella Kocak &amp; Kemal, 2008 (Mantodea: Mantidae, Photinainae). Zootaxa, 2529, 65 - 68." type="journal article" year="2010" yearSuffix="a">
Rivera (
<number box="[1357,1416,1187,1211]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" value="2010.0">2010</number>
a)
</bibRefCitation>
discussed all the resulting historical nomenclatural issues upon rediscovering the “lost” publication where 
<bibRefCitation author="Piza" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" refString="Piza, S. de T. Jr. (1982) A mantid new to Pernambuco (Mantodea, Mantidae, Eremiaphilinae) Margaromantis margaritaria, new taxa, Brazil. Ecossistema, 7 (1), 98." type="journal article" year="1982">
Piza (
<number box="[159,217,1259,1283]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" value="1982.0">1982</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authority="Piza, 1982" authorityName="Piza" authorityYear="1982" box="[350,810,1258,1283]" class="Insecta" family="Mantidae" genus="Margaromantis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mantodea" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="margaritaria">
<emphasis box="[350,678,1260,1283]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="345">Margaromantis margaritaria</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Piza" box="[686,810,1258,1283]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" refString="Piza, S. de T. Jr. (1982) A mantid new to Pernambuco (Mantodea, Mantidae, Eremiaphilinae) Margaromantis margaritaria, new taxa, Brazil. Ecossistema, 7 (1), 98." type="journal article" year="1982">
Piza, 
<number box="[750,810,1259,1283]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" value="1982.0">1982</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. After a detailed analysis of this publication, including the 
<typeStatus box="[196,294,1294,1319]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Rivera" authorityName="Rivera" authorityYear="2010" box="[340,718,1294,1319]" class="Insecta" family="Mantidae" genus="Margaromantis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mantodea" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="margaritaria">
<emphasis box="[340,526,1295,1318]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="345">M. margaritaria</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Rivera" box="[545,718,1294,1319]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" refString="Rivera, J. (2010 a) Lost and Found: Rediscovery of the genus Margaromantis Piza, 1982 and the consequential nomenclatural changes in the genus Colombiella Kocak &amp; Kemal, 2008 (Mantodea: Mantidae, Photinainae). Zootaxa, 2529, 65 - 68." type="journal article" year="2010" yearSuffix="a">
Rivera (
<number box="[639,698,1295,1319]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" value="2010.0">2010</number>
a)
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
concluded that the combination 
<taxonomicName authority="Piza, 1982" authorityName="Piza" authorityYear="1982" class="Insecta" family="Mantidae" genus="Margaromantis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mantodea" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="planicephala">
<emphasis box="[1105,1435,1294,1319]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="345">Margaromantis planicephala</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Piza" box="[159,283,1330,1355]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" refString="Piza, S. de T. Jr. (1982) A mantid new to Pernambuco (Mantodea, Mantidae, Eremiaphilinae) Margaromantis margaritaria, new taxa, Brazil. Ecossistema, 7 (1), 98." type="journal article" year="1982">
Piza, 
<number box="[226,283,1331,1355]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" value="1982.0">1982</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
should be the valid name for this species, placing 
<taxonomicName box="[887,994,1330,1355]" class="Insecta" family="Mantidae" genus="Rehniella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mantodea" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[887,994,1330,1355]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="345">Rehniella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis box="[1014,1076,1332,1355]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="345">sensu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lombardo" box="[1087,1280,1330,1355]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" refString="Lombardo, F. (1999) Remarks on the genus Metriomantis Saussure &amp; Zehntner and descriptions of two new species and a new genus: Rehniella gen. n. (Insecta: Mantodea). Revue Suisse de Zoologie, 106, 393 - 405." type="journal article" year="1999">
Lombardo, 
<number box="[1221,1280,1331,1355]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" value="1999.0">1999</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; non 
<bibRefCitation author="Hebard" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" refString="Hebard, M. (1928) The group Luzarae of the subfamily Phalangosinae (Orthoptera: Gryllidae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 54, 1 - 56." type="journal article" year="1928">
Hebard, 
<number box="[151,210,1367,1391]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" value="1928.0">1928</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), 
<emphasis box="[231,370,1366,1391]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="345">Colombiella</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[426,556,1366,1391]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="345">Lombardoa</emphasis>
under synonymy of 
<taxonomicName box="[791,965,1367,1390]" class="Insecta" family="Mantidae" genus="Margaromantis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mantodea" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[791,965,1367,1390]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="345">Margaromantis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1021,1204,1367,1390]" class="Insecta" family="Mantidae" genus="Margaromantis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mantodea" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="margaritaria">
<emphasis box="[1021,1204,1367,1390]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="345">M. margaritaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Mantidae" genus="Margaromantis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mantodea" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="planicephala">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="345">M. planicephala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,898,1823]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345">
During the course of our investigations, we had the opportunity to study the 
<typeStatus box="[1086,1134,1439,1463]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345">type</typeStatus>
material corresponding to 
<taxonomicName box="[151,373,1474,1499]" class="Insecta" family="Mantidae" genus="Photiomantis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mantodea" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silvai">
<emphasis box="[151,373,1474,1499]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="345">Photiomantis silvai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Piza" box="[544,696,1474,1499]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" refString="Piza, S. de T. Jr. (1968 b) Nova Photininae Brasileira (Mantidae). Revista de Agricultura, 43 (2), 49 - 50." type="journal article" year="1968" yearSuffix="b">
Piza (
<number box="[613,672,1474,1499]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" value="1968.0">1968</number>
b)
</bibRefCitation>
, a species later transferred to 
<taxonomicName box="[1059,1176,1474,1499]" class="Insecta" family="Mantidae" genus="Photinella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mantodea" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1059,1176,1474,1499]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="345">Photinella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Terra" box="[1228,1377,1474,1499]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" refString="Terra, P. S. (1995) Revisao Sistematica dos Generos de Louva-a - Deus da Regiao Neotropical. (Mantodea). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 39, 13 - 94." type="journal article" year="1995">
Terra (
<number box="[1307,1368,1474,1499]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" value="1995.0">1995</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Our analysis of this 
<typeStatus box="[335,383,1511,1535]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345">type</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation box="[401,470,1510,1535]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1740,1762]" captionTargetBox="[166,1435,1214,1714]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,1213,1718]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 8. Metriomantis planicephala (now Photiomantis planicephala): a) holotype ♀, dorsal habitus, from Ceará-Mirim, Rio Grande do Norte, Brazil (ANSP). Photiomantis silvai (now Photiomantis planicephala): b) holotype ♂, dorsal habitus, from Piauí, Brazil (ESALQ). Margaromantis margaritaria (now Photiomantis planicephala): c) holotype ♂, dorsal habitus, from Petrolima, Pernambuco, Brazil (ESALQ)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/239055/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="345">
Fig. 
<number box="[457,470,1510,1535]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
b) and additional material made necessary a closer reexamination of the 
<typeStatus box="[1315,1363,1511,1535]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Mantidae" genus="Margaromantis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mantodea" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="margaritaria">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="345">M. margaritaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[315,384,1546,1571]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1740,1762]" captionTargetBox="[166,1435,1214,1714]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,1213,1718]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 8. Metriomantis planicephala (now Photiomantis planicephala): a) holotype ♀, dorsal habitus, from Ceará-Mirim, Rio Grande do Norte, Brazil (ANSP). Photiomantis silvai (now Photiomantis planicephala): b) holotype ♂, dorsal habitus, from Piauí, Brazil (ESALQ). Margaromantis margaritaria (now Photiomantis planicephala): c) holotype ♂, dorsal habitus, from Petrolima, Pernambuco, Brazil (ESALQ)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/239055/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="345">
Fig. 
<number box="[370,384,1547,1571]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
c) in addition to topotypical material of 
<taxonomicName box="[853,1160,1546,1571]" class="Insecta" family="Mantidae" genus="Metriomantis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mantodea" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="planicephala">
<emphasis box="[853,1160,1546,1571]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="345">Metriomantis planicephala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1180,1249,1546,1571]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1393,1415]" captionTargetBox="[273,1297,228,1343]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[253,1334,195,1371]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 9. Structures of the phallic complex and variation of pseudophallus in ventral view: a) left epiphallus, and b) hypophallus of topotypical male of Photiomantis planicephala, c) pseudophallus of Photiomantis silvai (now Photiomantis planicephala); d) pseudophallus of Margaromantis margaritaria (now Photiomantis planicephala) (ESALQ)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/239056/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="345">
Fig. 
<number box="[1235,1249,1546,1571]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
a–d), as they all seemed to correspond to one single species. Indeed, we could not detect any relevant difference in the constitution of the male genitalia that cannot be attributed to intraspecific geographic variation (
<figureCitation box="[1102,1169,1618,1643]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1393,1415]" captionTargetBox="[273,1297,228,1343]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[253,1334,195,1371]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 9. Structures of the phallic complex and variation of pseudophallus in ventral view: a) left epiphallus, and b) hypophallus of topotypical male of Photiomantis planicephala, c) pseudophallus of Photiomantis silvai (now Photiomantis planicephala); d) pseudophallus of Margaromantis margaritaria (now Photiomantis planicephala) (ESALQ)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/239056/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="345">
Fig. 
<number box="[1155,1169,1618,1643]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
c–d). Consequently, the name 
<taxonomicName box="[227,376,1654,1679]" class="Insecta" family="Mantidae" genus="Photiomantis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mantodea" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[227,376,1654,1679]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="345">Photiomantis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here resurrected from synonymy and, in accordance to the “Principle of Priority”, 
<taxonomicName authority="Rehn, 1916" authorityName="Rehn" authorityYear="1916" box="[151,608,1690,1715]" class="Insecta" family="Mantidae" genus="Photiomantis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mantodea" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="planicephala">
<emphasis box="[151,453,1690,1715]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="345">Photiomantis planicephala</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rehn" box="[468,600,1690,1715]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" refString="Rehn, J. A. G. (1916) The Stanford Expedition to Brazil, 1911 Dermaptera and Orthoptera I, Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia, 42, 257 - 266." type="journal article" year="1916">
Rehn, 
<number box="[543,600,1690,1715]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" value="1916.0">1916</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
is now the valid name for this species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,898,1823]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345">
More recently, 
<bibRefCitation author="Menezes" box="[368,653,1726,1751]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" refString="Menezes, E. da C. &amp; Bravo, F. (2015) A new species of Margaromantis Piza, 1982 (Insecta: Mantodea) from Brazil. Biodiversity Data Journal, 3, 1 - 9." type="journal article" year="2015">
Menezes &amp; Bravo (
<number box="[586,645,1726,1751]" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" value="2015.0">2015</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName box="[773,1091,1726,1751]" class="Insecta" family="Mantidae" genus="Margaromantis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mantodea" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrolineata">
<emphasis box="[773,1091,1726,1751]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="345">Margaromantis nigrolineata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from northeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1304,1376,1726,1751]" name="Brazil" pageId="10" pageNumber="345">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. This is a valid species, but referable instead to 
<taxonomicName box="[618,767,1762,1787]" class="Insecta" family="Mantidae" genus="Photiomantis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mantodea" pageId="10" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[618,767,1762,1787]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="345">Photiomantis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
